;; tsukuru 作 — public-directory manufacturer candidates (reference dataset, R0)
;; :sourcing :public-directory — NOT authoritative, NOT onboarded/registered on tsukuru (G10).
;; Every entry is a REAL company; every fact (country/ISIC/capabilities) is drawn from that
;; company's own public site or Wikipedia — cited in :factory/source-url for verification.
;; :factory/did here uses a "candidate:manufacturer-directory/..." id, deliberately NOT a
;; did:web:tsukuru.etzhayyim.com/... path, because these companies have not consented to or
;; been onboarded into the tsukuru registry — this is a research/reference directory only,
;; not a claim of platform membership.
;; :factory/labor-provenance is :unknown for every entry — public corporate/industry facts do
;; not establish labor conditions or ESG posture, and none is asserted here (G8).
;; No :factory/fulfillment-modes is asserted — BTO/MTO/CTO capability is a tsukuru-integration
;; fact, not a public-directory fact, and is left unset rather than guessed.
;; Compiled 2026-07-08 via public web research (company sites + Wikipedia), one source_url per
;; entry. Batch 1: 80 companies / 18 countries / 12 ISIC divisions (medium pilot, per owner
;; scope). Batch 2 (/loop pass 2): +32 companies / +11 countries (BR MX ES PL CZ NL CH AT TR IL
;; SG) / +4 ISIC divisions (C10 food, C20 chemicals, C24 basic metals, C32 other manufacturing).
;; Batch 3 (/loop pass 3): +32 companies / +9 countries (CA AU PT ZA BE SA AE QA EG) / +6 ISIC
;; divisions (C11 beverages, C12 tobacco, C16 wood/cork, C18 printing, C19 coke/petroleum, C23
;; non-metallic minerals). Batch 4 (/loop pass 4): +32 companies / +15 countries (BD KH LK PH NG
;; KE GH CL AR CO PE RO HU SK SI) / +1 ISIC division (C14 apparel, closing the gap called out
;; after batch 3). Batch 5 (/loop pass 5): +32 companies / +11 countries (LT LV EE BG HR RS PK
;; ET TZ UG CI) — pure regional-depth pass, no new ISIC divisions. Batch 6 (/loop pass 6): +32
;; companies / +10 countries (MA TN JO LB DZ SN CM ZM ZW RW) — half depth-in-major-economies
;; (US +8 in previously-uncovered industries: machinery/semiconductors/chemicals/pharma/food/
;; paper/furniture/electrical; CN +8 likewise: steel/petrochemicals/computers/cement/heavy-
;; machinery/food/beverages), half remaining-country-gap fill (Maghreb/Levant, remaining
;; Sub-Saharan Africa). Running total: 240 companies / 74 countries / 23 ISIC divisions.
;; Only C33 (repair/installation of machinery — arguably a service, not primary manufacturing)
;; remains uncovered, likely permanently by design. Country coverage is now broad (74) and
;; roughly proportional to global manufacturing output for major economies (JP/DE/CN/US/IN/IT
;; each have 8-9 entries); future batches should keep splitting between (a) depth in
;; already-listed major economies — plenty of real, well-documented companies remain
;; unlisted per country, and this is what actually moves toward the original registry's
;; "460+ manufacturers" scale reference. Batch 7 (/loop pass 7): +32 companies / +9 countries
;; (KZ UZ GE AZ DO TT MK BA AL) — same split: DE +8 (chemicals/pharma/steel/electronics/
;; semiconductors/optics/food/adhesives, previously all automotive/machinery) and IN +8
;; (steel/aluminium/cement/petrochemicals/paints/food/EMS, previously all pharma/textiles/
;; auto) for economy depth; Central Asia+Caucasus and Caribbean+remaining-Balkans for country
;; gaps. Running total: 272 companies / 83 countries / 23 ISIC divisions.
;; Batch 8 (/loop pass 8): +33 companies / +8 countries (IS LU CY MT MN FJ PG JM) — JP +8
;; (automotive/steel/chemicals/pharma/food/beverages/shipbuilding/tires, previously all
;; robotics/precision-machining/electronics/printing) and KR +8 (automotive/steel/
;; petrochemicals/shipbuilding/home-electronics, previously all semiconductors/electronics/
;; tobacco) for economy depth; small-but-real economies (Iceland aluminum smelting,
;; Luxembourg steel/tires, Cyprus/Malta brewing+cement+rubber, Mongolia/Fiji/PNG/Jamaica
;; mining-adjacent metals and food/beverage) for country-gap fill — deliberately not padded
;; to a round number where the real company count ran out (9 in the small-Europe cluster, not
;; forced to 8). Running total: 305 companies / 91 countries / 23 ISIC divisions, zero
;; duplicate DIDs.
;; Remaining country gaps: Russia/CIS, Iran, and North Korea (politically sensitive — skip
;; pending explicit owner direction), Haiti and Cuba (Caribbean remainder — Cuba politically
;; sensitive, treat like Russia/Iran pending owner direction), a handful of very small states
;; (Andorra, San Marino, Monaco, Liechtenstein — likely no meaningful primary manufacturing to
;; find). With virtually every significant manufacturing economy now represented, future
;; batches should default to economy-depth (any already-listed country, new industries) —
;; that is the real lever left toward the original registry's "460+ manufacturers" scale
;; reference — rather than chasing ever-smaller remaining-country gaps.
;; Batch 9 (/loop pass 9): +32 companies, +0 new countries (pure depth + thin-ISIC pass, using
;; kotoba/coverage_report.bb output to target it) — GB +8 (pharma/chemicals/steel/food, vs.
;; existing aerospace/auto/tobacco), FR +8 (pharma/industrial-gases/food/luxury-leather, vs.
;; existing aerospace/auto/spirits), TW +8 (petrochemicals/steel/bicycles/food, vs. existing
;; all-semiconductor), plus 8 companies specifically closing the four thinnest ISIC divisions
;; flagged by the coverage report: C12 tobacco (+2: Japan Tobacco, Philip Morris
;; International), C18 printing (+2: RR Donnelley, Quad/Graphics), C19 petroleum refining
;; (+2: Indian Oil Corporation, Valero Energy), C25 fabricated metal products (+2: Crown
;; Holdings, Stanley Black & Decker). Running total: 337 companies / 91 countries / 23 ISIC
;; divisions, zero duplicate DIDs.
;; Batch 10 (/loop pass 10): +30 companies, +0 new countries — BR+MX depth (Braskem, Suzano,
;; Alpargatas, Hypera Pharma, Alpek, Vitro, Grupo Flexi, Genomma Lab — petrochemicals/paper/
;; footwear/pharma/glass); thin-ISIC C15 leather +4 (ECCO, Coach, Clarks, Camper) and C32 other
;; manufacturing +4 (Yamaha, LEGO, Stryker, Head Sport); second entry for 9 single-entry
;; countries — got real, distinct companies for all 9 (Cementos Pacasmayo PE, Condor
;; Electronics DZ, Alucam CM, Bralirwa RW, Bosnalijek BA, Guinness Ghana Breweries GH, Birra
;; Tirana AL, Cambrew KH, INDEVCO Group LB); thin-ISIC round 2b targeting C16/C17/C19/C22 — only
;; 5 of the requested 8 survived dedup (Oji Holdings C17, Metsä Wood C16, Orlen C19, Michelin
;; C22, Amcor C22); the agent's "Suzano" and "Canfor" picks were the same companies already
;; added earlier in this batch / in batch 6, and its "Reliance Industries" pick for C19
;; collided with the existing in/reliance-industries (added batch 7, different ISIC) — all
;; three dropped rather than silently double-counted (per-batch agent prompts list explicit
;; avoid-lists, but they're necessarily incomplete against a 300+-entry file; this dedup pass
;; is why kotoba/validate_candidates.bb's duplicate-DID check runs before every commit).
;; Running total: 367 companies / 91 countries / 23 ISIC divisions, zero duplicate DIDs.
;; Batch 11 (/loop pass 11): +31 companies, +0 new countries — CA+DK+CH depth (Apotex, Buhler
;; Industries, Saputo, Novo Nordisk, Arla Foods, Novartis, Bühler Group, Nestlé — pharma/
;; agri-machinery/dairy-food); ES+PL+LK depth (Porcelanosa, Ebro Foods, Ercros, Grupa Azoty,
;; Maspex, Cersanit, Dilmah, DSI Samson Group — ceramics/food/chemicals/tea/tires, Sri Lanka's
;; first non-apparel entries); thin-ISIC round 3 across C12/C16/C18/C19/C22/C25/C31 (Imperial
;; Brands, Altria, Dai Nippon Printing, Walstead Group, Bertelsmann Printing Group, ASSA ABLOY,
;; Fiskars, Tramontina, MillerKnoll, Kinnarps, Egger Group, West Fraser Timber, Phillips 66,
;; Pirelli, Hankook Tire). Dropped one more agent pick ("Reliance Industries" for C19, again —
;; third time this exact company has resurfaced across batches 9-11 as an obvious go-to
;; "famous refiner" example) after the validator's duplicate-DID check would have caught it;
;; per-batch avoid-lists remain necessarily incomplete against a 350+-entry file, so every
;; batch's new picks get grepped against the merged main candidates.edn before being appended,
;; not just validated after the fact. Running total: 398 companies / 91 countries / 23 ISIC
;; divisions, zero duplicate DIDs.
;; Batch 12 (/loop pass 12): +32 companies, +2 new countries (IE, HK) — third entry for 19
;; countries that had exactly 2 (mostly pharma/food/automotive/electricals, filling gaps left
;; by earlier cement/textile/electronics-heavy batches): Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand,
;; Philippines, Singapore, Vietnam, Saudi Arabia, UAE, Jordan, Uganda, North Macedonia,
;; Algeria, Egypt, Uzbekistan, Tunisia, Morocco, Côte d'Ivoire, Kazakhstan; thin-ISIC round 4
;; across C12/C16/C17/C18/C19/C25/C31/C32. Ireland enters the dataset via Smurfit Westrock
;; (paper) and Cimpress (printing); Hong Kong via Man Wah Holdings (furniture).
;; Dropped 4 duplicate agent picks this batch (Qatar Steel, Bosnalijek, Sinopec, and — a FOURTH
;; time — Reliance Industries) via the pre-append grep against merged main. The recurring
;; Reliance Industries collisions (batches 9, 10, 11, 12) confirm it's simply the most
;; "obvious" real example for oil-refining/petrochemical prompts; rather than keep expanding
;; avoid-lists, every batch's raw picks get grepped against candidates.edn before appending —
;; that step is now non-negotiable, not just for spot-checks.
;; Running total: 430 companies / 93 countries / 23 ISIC divisions, zero duplicate DIDs — within
;; 30 of the original registry's "460+ manufacturers" scale reference.
;; Batch 13 (/loop pass 13): +34 companies, +1 new country (KW) — third entry for 18
;; previously-2-entry countries across Central/Eastern Europe+Caucasus (pharma-heavy: Krka,
;; Gedeon Richter, Antibiotice, Grindeks, Saneca — plus Azersun food, Preciosa crystal glass,
;; DuPont Luxembourg nonwovens, Playmobil Malta toys, Kerry Group Ireland food ingredients) and
;; Latin America+Caribbean+Pacific+Hong Kong (Michell y Cía Peru alpaca textiles, Tecnoquímicas
;; Colombia pharma, Johnson Electric Hong Kong motors, SQM Chile lithium chemicals, PNG Forest
;; Products, Pratima Fiji pharma, La Aurora Dominican cigars, Wisynco Jamaica plastics); thin-
;; ISIC round 5 across C12/C15/C17/C18/C19/C25/C32, adding Kuwait (Kuwait National Petroleum,
;; C19) as a new country. Dropped 2 more duplicate agent picks (IDS Borjomi Georgia and
;; Methanol Holdings Trinidad — both re-surfaced from batches 7/8) via the pre-append grep.
;; **This batch crosses the original registry's "460+ manufacturers" scale reference**: running
;; total 464 companies / 94 countries / 23 ISIC divisions, zero duplicate DIDs. Country count
;; (94) already far exceeds the "30+ countries" reference from the same source. This is still
;; :sourcing :public-directory reference data, not the onboarded/live :factory registry — see
;; the file header above and CLAUDE.md's Manufacturer Registry Rules — but the scale target
;; that originally motivated the "460+" figure in manifest.edn/CLAUDE.md is now matched by real,
;; sourced, verifiable public-directory entries rather than an unverified legacy assumption.
;; Batch 14 (/loop pass 14): with the scale milestone passed, shifted weight from raw growth
;; toward maturity: kotoba/validate_candidates.bb gained a near-duplicate-display-name check
;; (normalized, case/punctuation-insensitive) alongside the existing duplicate-:factory/did
;; check — a spot audit of all 464 prior entries found zero near-duplicates, confirming the
;; batch-10-onward pre-append-grep discipline has been working, but the check is now permanent
;; and automatic rather than a manual step. Also +29 companies, +0 new countries: fourth entry
;; for 21 places that had exactly 2 (Trinidad/Mongolia/Tanzania/Georgia/Qatar/Cameroon/
;; Zimbabwe/Rwanda/Bosnia/Kenya/Cyprus/Ghana/Albania/Cambodia/Lebanon/Norway/Ethiopia/Senegal/
;; Zambia/Hong Kong/Serbia, skewed toward cement/brewing/basic-metals/chemicals/pharma to
;; diversify each place's industry mix); thin-ISIC round 6 across C14/C16/C25/C31.
;; Running total: 493 companies / 94 countries / 23 ISIC divisions, zero duplicate DIDs, zero
;; near-duplicate display names.
;; Batch 15 (/loop pass 15): +12 companies, +0 new countries. Kuwait depth (EQUATE
;; Petrochemical, Kuwait Cement — was down to 1 entry, now 3) plus thin-ISIC round 7 across
;; C12/C15/C17/C18/C19. Dropped 2 more duplicate agent picks: Reliance Industries for C19 — a
;; FIFTH recurrence across batches 9/10/11/12/13/15 (it keeps coming back because it's simply
;; the most obvious real "world's largest refinery" example for any petroleum-refining prompt)
;; — and Amcor for C18, which already exists under C22 (added batch 10). Maturity: adds
;; kotoba/check_source_urls.bb, a periodic/manual link-reachability checker (curl HEAD/GET per
;; :factory/source-url, 8s timeout) — deliberately NOT wired into CI since HTTP checks are
;; inherently flaky (rate-limiting, bot-blocking) and a transient 403 doesn't mean an entry's
;; underlying fact is wrong; it's a "worth a human glance" signal, not a hard gate.
;; Running total: 505 companies / 94 countries / 23 ISIC divisions, zero duplicate DIDs.
;; Batch 16 (/loop pass 16): +16 companies, +0 new countries. First full kotoba/
;; check_source_urls.bb run reported 477/505 clean (96.8%); the 16 flagged were all curl-vs-WAF
;; false positives (403/000 from corporate anti-bot protection), not dead sources — noted in
;; the script's own header so future runs don't re-investigate the same pattern. Thin-ISIC
;; round 8 across C19/C22/C31/C32 (Ecopetrol, Petron, Nokian Tyres, Apollo Tyres, IKEA
;; Industry, Nitori, Getinge, Steinway & Sons). Sweden+Turkey+Thailand depth (Scania, SSAB,
;; Sobi, Ford Otosan, Erdemir, Arçelik, Charoen Pokphand Foods, Sahaviriya Steel).
;; Running total: 521 companies / 94 countries / 23 ISIC divisions, zero duplicate DIDs.
;; Batch 17 (/loop pass 17): +26 companies, +1 new country (GR). Fourth entry for 14
;; previously-3-entry countries (Balkans+Baltics+Portugal+Israel, Peru-region+North
;; Africa+Argentina+Chile — chemicals/basic-metals/cement heavy). Thin-ISIC round 9 across
;; C12/C14/C16/C17/C18/C25. Greece enters via Karelia Tobacco Company.
;; Dropped 6 duplicate agent picks this batch — the highest count yet, but all legitimate
;; near-misses rather than the same-company-re-suggested pattern from before: ICL Dead Sea
;; Works (same real facility as the already-listed ICL Group, il/icl-group, just described at
;; subsidiary granularity) and Metsä Group (same corporate family as the already-listed Metsä
;; Wood, fi/metsa-wood, parent vs. business-unit) were judgment calls — same country, same
;; underlying enterprise, would read as double-counting even with a different :factory/did
;; slug and a name the near-duplicate-name checker wouldn't catch (different display names).
;; The other 4 (Michell y Cía, Ciments du Maroc, Interloop, Vinatex) were literal re-adds of
;; already-listed companies. This is a reminder that grep-for-collision only catches identical
;; or near-identical name strings — parent/subsidiary and holding-company/brand relationships
;; still need a human judgment call, which is why every batch's picks get read, not just grepped.
;; Running total: 547 companies / 95 countries / 23 ISIC divisions, zero duplicate DIDs.
;; See kotoba/validate_candidates.bb (batch 4), kotoba/coverage_report.bb (batch 8 — prints the
;; per-country/per-ISIC breakdown used to plan each batch, so future passes don't need to
;; hand-run ad hoc bb -e queries) and .github/workflows/validate-candidates.yml (batch 5,
;; fixed in the batch-5 PR after the first CI run failed on a nonexistent
;; babashka/setup-babashka action — now uses the official install script) for the automated
;; consistency check and its CI enforcement.

